# FOSS & Privacy Compliance

## License

- Pure FOSS under **GPL-3.0-or-later** (OBDForge product license; do not rewrite to MIT)
- No proprietary closed-source SDKs in production path
- Android: no Google Play Services, Firebase, or closed telemetry trackers

## Distribution

- GitHub Releases as primary channel
- Platform-appropriate: F-Droid, Winget, GitHub Pages, package indexes

## Privacy & Telemetry

- Opt-in only telemetry — never enabled by default
- GDPR/CCPA compliant data handling
- No PII in logs without explicit user consent

## Security

- Secrets never committed (Gitleaks pre-commit enforced)
- Dependency scanning via CodeQL and Trivy
- Input validation at all data boundaries

## Android FOSS (when Module A active)

- Use UnifiedPush or native OS providers instead of proprietary push
- Reproducible builds with SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH
- Lock compiler toolchains with cryptographic hashes
